## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 2 (systemic — affects all 10 tests) |
| **Medium** | 2 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is invoked exactly once, achieving line coverage, but almost nothing is actually verified. These tests will never fail regardless of bugs in the production code.

---

### 🔴 Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage Touching (Systemic)

All 10 tests march through the public API surface in declaration order with either **zero assertions** or only a trivial `Assert.IsNotNull`. The intent is (perhaps unintentionally) to inflate the coverage metric rather than verify behavior.

**Tests with NO assertions at all (6/10):**

| Test Method | Line | What it misses |
|---|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` | 17 | Never verifies the product was persisted |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` | 31 | Never verifies the price actually changed |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` | 38 | Never verifies the product is gone |
| `GetProductCount_Works` | 62 | Gets count, discards it |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | 68 | Never verifies discounted prices |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` | 85 | Never verifies imported products exist |

#### 2. Trivial `IsNotNull`-Only Assertions (4/10)

| Test Method | Line | Problem |
|---|---|---|
| `GetProduct_Works` | 28 | Doesn't verify SKU, Name, or Price of the returned product |
| `SearchProducts_Works` | 51 | Doesn't verify result count or content |
| `GetAllProducts_Works` | 59 | Doesn't verify the collection has 1 item |
| `ExportToCsv_Works` | 81 | Doesn't verify the CSV string is well-formed |

---

### Concrete Fixes (Before → After)

**`AddProduct_Works` → verify round-trip:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_ProductIsRetrievable()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var retrieved = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", retrieved?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, retrieved?.Price);
}
```

**`UpdatePrice_Works` → verify mutation:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_ChangesStoredPrice()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated?.Price);
}
```

**`RemoveProduct_Works` → verify deletion:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
